Name: bile duct signet ring cell carcinoma
Definition: An adenocarcinoma that derives_from epithelial cells originating in glandular tissue
Synonym: bile duct Signet Ring cell carcinoma

Name: extrahepatic bile duct carcinoma
Definition: A breast carcinoma that represents a mixed group of malignant neoplasms characterized by the histologic presence of two or more cellular types.

Name: bile duct adenocarcinoma
Definition: A bile duct carcinoma that derives_from epithelial cells of glandular origin.

Name: squamous cell bile duct carcinoma
Definition: A squamous cell carcinoma that is located_in the bile duct.

Name: distal biliary tract carcinoma
Definition: An uterine corpus leiomyomatosis that is located throughout the uterine corpus.
Synonym: carcinoma of the Distal biliary tract

Name: obsolete recurrent extrahepatic bile duct cancer
Definition: An uterine corpus leiomyomatosis that is located throughout the uterine corpus.
